		<title></title>
		<content> Don’t make the common mistake of first subtracting      the Applicable Exclusion Amount and then calculating      the tax.   First calculate the tax.  Then, subtract the Applicable      Credit. Credit vs. Exclusion Don’t Confuse the Credit with the Exclusion Only the Applicable Credit is used on the Estate Tax Return. </content>
		<related-content>It&amp;#x20;is&amp;#x20;quite&amp;#x20;common&amp;#x20;for&amp;#x20;people&amp;#x20;to&amp;#x20;confuse&amp;#x20;the&amp;#x20;applicable&amp;#x20;credit&amp;#x20;amount&amp;#x20;with&amp;#x20;the&amp;#x20;applicable&amp;#x20;exclusion&amp;#x20;amount.&amp;#x20;But&amp;#x20;the&amp;#x20;difference&amp;#x20;is&amp;#x20;significant:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;[click]&amp;#x20;Only&amp;#x20;the&amp;#x20;applicable&amp;#x20;credit&amp;#x20;amount&amp;#x20;is&amp;#x20;actually&amp;#x20;used&amp;#x20;in&amp;#x20;the&amp;#x20;tax&amp;#x20;calculation;&amp;#x20;the&amp;#x20;applicable&amp;#x20;exclusion&amp;#x20;amount&amp;#x20;simply&amp;#x20;illustrates&amp;#x20;the&amp;#x20;amount&amp;#x20;of&amp;#x20;estate&amp;#x20;assets&amp;#x20;that&amp;#x20;are&amp;#x20;covered&amp;#x20;by&amp;#x20;the&amp;#x20;credit.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;[click]&amp;#x20;A&amp;#x20;very&amp;#x20;common&amp;#x20;mistake&amp;#x20;is&amp;#x20;for&amp;#x20;people&amp;#x20;to&amp;#x20;first&amp;#x20;subtract&amp;#x20;the&amp;#x20;applicable&amp;#x20;exclusion&amp;#x20;amount&amp;#x20;from&amp;#x20;the&amp;#x20;gross&amp;#x20;estate,&amp;#x20;and&amp;#x20;then&amp;#x20;compute&amp;#x20;the&amp;#x20;tax.&amp;#x20;&amp;#x20;This&amp;#x20;results&amp;#x20;in&amp;#x20;a&amp;#x20;significantly&amp;#x20;lower&amp;#x20;tax&amp;#x20;bill.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;[click]&amp;#x20;Remember&amp;#x20;that&amp;#x20;in&amp;#x20;calculating&amp;#x20;the&amp;#x20;tax&amp;#x20;you&amp;#x20;add&amp;#x20;all&amp;#x20;lifetime&amp;#x20;taxable&amp;#x20;gifts&amp;#x20;to&amp;#x20;the&amp;#x20;final&amp;#x20;estate,&amp;#x20;and&amp;#x20;then&amp;#x20;compute&amp;#x20;the&amp;#x20;tax&amp;#x20;on&amp;#x20;the&amp;#x20;total.&amp;#x20;Only&amp;#x20;then&amp;#x20;is&amp;#x20;the&amp;#x20;applicable&amp;#x20;credit&amp;#x20;amount&amp;#x20;applied&amp;#x20;against&amp;#x20;the&amp;#x20;tax.&amp;#x20;&lt;br&gt;</related-content>
